com.nokia.maps.routing.enums

Interface RouteFeatureWeight


  • public interface RouteFeatureWeight
    This interface defines the route feature weights. Route feature weights are used to define weighted conditions on special route features like "tollroad", "motorways", etc. (see type RouteFeature for a complete list) that the calculated route is supposed to fulfill.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int AVOID
      This constant indicates the routing engine assigns penalties for links with the corresponding feature.
      static int NORMAL
      This constant indicates the routing engine neither prefers nor avoids or excludes links with the corresponding feature.
      static int PREFER
      This constant indicates the routing engine prefers links with the corresponding route feature.
      static int SOFTEXCLUDE
      This constant indicates the routing engine does not consider links with the corresponding feature.
      static int STRICT_EXCLUDE
      This constant indicates the routing algorithm guarantees that strictly excluded features won't be part of the resulting route.

    • Field Detail

      • STRICT_EXCLUDE

        static final int STRICT_EXCLUDE
        This constant indicates the routing algorithm guarantees that strictly excluded features won't be part of the resulting route. If this condition cannot be fulfilled no route is returned. "HOVLanes" and "stairs" are examples for features where a strict exclusion might be required.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SOFTEXCLUDE

        static final int SOFTEXCLUDE
        This constant indicates the routing engine does not consider links with the corresponding feature. If no route can be found because of these limitations the condition is weakened.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        static final int AVOID
